    public class NativePeer
extends Object
implements Cloneable
    native peer classes are part of MJI and contain the code that is executed by the host VM (i.e. outside the state-tracked JPF VM). Each class executed by JPF that has native mehods must have a native peer class (which is looked up and associated at class loadtime)
